DCI detectives on Thursday arrested three people in Runyenjes town following a robbery targetting a businessman in Isiolo. Jamawin Kinyua, Winnie Kinyua, and Salome Nkonge were arrested while driving the stolen motor vehicle. "The suspects were armed with a pistol and a Swiss Army knife," DCI tweeted.  A gun recovered from three suspects arrested in Runyenjes for robbery on Thursday, October 4, 2018. /DCI "They also robbed the victim of his a phone and cash. They will be charged with robbery with violence on Friday." DCI detectives are still looking for the other suspects who escaped.  An army knife and car keys recovered from three suspects arrested in Runyenjes for robbery on Thursday, October 4, 2018. /DCI Click here for the latest political news